{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, models that have a greater number of parameters tend to surpass the performance of those with fewer parameters.",
    "Comparison of the results with the state-ofthe-artIn this section, we compare our results with the baseline method [3].",
    "The baseline study employed an unsupervised FastText model, which generally is less suited for categorical classification tasks.",
    "In comparison, our supervised FAST-RNN model when implemented with optimal regularization and hyperparameter tuning outperformed the baseline in terms of both accuracy and macro F1-score.",
    "The FAST-RNN model achieves a Macro F1-Score of 0.97 for the 'Hateful' category, far surpassing the baseline models' scores of 0.08 for BiLSTM and 0.06 for CNN-LSTM."
  ]
}